location.name: Villa Salavina, Santiago del Estero, AR (-28,801, -63,426)

mediaNotes:
NOTES: The area is natural pampas (grasslands) with gallery forests and forest islands, also influenced by chaco (dry forest) of southern Bolivia.  All of the area is highly grazed and burnt anually.  Most of the birds, especially the Psittacids, were found in forest islands, often dominated by what the locals call Motacu palms, which have plentiful fruits. 

These recordings were made at a secret location of the threatened political endemic Ara glaucogularis site.  Further information on the location must be obtained through Alan Hesse at Armonia (Bolivia BirdLife partner) at armonia@scbbs-bo.com . Habitat: Savannah.
Recording of bird shown in photo

Dawn song from a thorn tree in Rincón del Socorro compound. Background includes: Chalk-browed Mockingbird, Sayaca Tanager, two-note, mechanical-sounding calls of Crested (S.) Caracara, deep two-note booms of Greater Rhea, cattle, et al. Recorded using a Fostex FR-2LE with a Sennheiser ME67 directional mic with an Auray shaggy windscreen.
